cc:Work.dc:description: vertical mass on spring system. (a) spring without mass showing natural length. (b) mass added to spring. gravitational force is acting on the mass, resulting in displacement of x. system is in equiliburm position. spring force and gravitational force cancel each other. (c) additional negative displacement of y leads to a positive restoring force.
